ğŸ“– ğŸš€ Part 4: Continuous Deployment (Release Pipeline)

 Step 8ï¸âƒ£: Create Release Pipeline
Go to Azure DevOps â†’ Releases
Click + New Pipeline
Start with an Empty job
Click Add an artifact

Source type: Build
Source: your CI pipeline
Default version: Latest
Click Add
Create a Stage
Name: Deploy to ACI
Click Tasks
Add Task: Azure CLI
Display name: Deploy ACI
Azure subscription: your service connection
Script type: Inline

Inline Script:
az container create --resource-group aci-dev-resources \
--name springbootaci \
--image financeregistry.azurecr.io/springbootapp:$(Build.BuildId) \
--registry-login-server financeregistry.azurecr.io \
--registry-username <acr-username> \
--registry-password <acr-password> \
--dns-name-label springbootaci-demo --ports 8080

 Step 9ï¸âƒ£: Enable Continuous Deployment Trigger
